To solve the dilemma of reconciling noise margin, power consumption, and propagation delay for mono-type inverters, researchers have proposed dual-gate[15] and dual-\$V_{{\rm TH}}\$
[16] OTFT technologies to control the \$V_{{\rm TH}}\$ of OTFTs for realizing both enhancement-mode and depletion-mode OTFTs in the same process, via tuning back-gate voltages or replacing the gate materials. (See the literature for the inverter schematics and corresponding transfer curves of dual-gate inverters.[15]
) Lowering the back-gate voltage can shift \$V_{{\rm TRIP}}\$ toward half-\$V_{{\rm DD}}\$ and therefore improve the noise margin.
